cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses statistical models for parsing and classification. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a framework for automated sentiment analysis. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is often used in information retrieval tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as sentiment analysis has implications for understanding human behavior and attitudes.
